@node "0" "What is cP!_PFS2Defrag ?"

@{b}What is @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} ???
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}
@{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} is a little Tool to defragment FILES on an
AFS/PFS2 Partition.

It's simple: @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} runs DiskValid. If a fragmented file
has been found on the Partition @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} copies these files
to T: and then back to the original Partition. AFS/PFS2 writes now the
files defragmented back.

@{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} was written in @{b}Arexx@{ub} and compiled with a
"Rexx2Executable" compiler !

The Size of the Sourcecode V1.0 is exactly xxxx bytes !
The Sourcecode V1.0 has exactly xxx lines !
The complete Sourcecode was written by hand :) with CygnusEd !

Note: The Archive is only @{b}COMPLETE@{ub} with these files:

cP!_PFS2Defrag
cP!_PFS2Defrag.Guide
cP!_PFS2Defrag.Guide.info
MD5SUM.CRC
MD5SUM.CRC.ASC.PGP2
MD5SUM.CRC.ASC.PGP5

If a file doesn't exist, you @{b}don't@{ub} have the ORIGINAL Version !
Please write me a EMail (campino@gmx.net) and I'll send you
the "right" Archive.
 
@endnode

@node "1" "System-Requirements"

@{b}Any System-Requirements ?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}
An Amiga :) (*)
OS 3.x (*) (not tested with OS 2.x)
RexxMast must be runnin' (*)
A Little Memory (*)
Rexxsupport.library (*)
AFS or PFS-II installed (*)

* = Not included :)

@endnode

@node "2" "Usage"

@{b}How Can I start @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} ?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}
- Start @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} from shell with
  @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} VOLUME/A:
  -> Where Volume is an Argument.
  e.g. @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} DH0: scans for fragmented files on DH0: and defragment's
  them !

@endnode

@node "3" "Installation"

@{b}How to install @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} ?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}
- Just copy @{i}cP!_PFS2Defrag@{ui} to your C: Directory and this Guide
  in Help: or somewhere :)

Simple, eh ? ;)

@endnode

